<subSubSection id="7A3E857AE84B2D6B78B5DE6D6E76A772" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="827A3BEA444D329B7E6C136938C36E7A" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="134BD57C186F92A4A87DAE81EC2F1303" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Larger body length, usually between 9.5-14 mm; mandibles with four teeth (plus molar one); pronotum usually as wide as long, sometimes longer than wide; elytra 3.9-4.2 times longer than wide, finely punctuate; aedeagus internal sac with stingray-like or u-shaped ventral spur and quadrangular central sclerite with lower sclerotized margin.</paragraph>
